				| , which means even more documentation can be found on their website. 


			section.buttons
				h2#buttons Buttons
				p Buttons are used to perform an action. For example, when submitting a form or examining data.
				.component
					h3 Primary action
					p Use these to direct your user to the most important actions on the page.
					button.btn.btn-primary Default
					button.btn.btn-primary.btn-xs Extra small
				.component
					h3 Secondary action
					p These acknowledge that there is an action to take, but that it's not the most important one.
					button.btn.btn-default Default
					button.btn.btn-default.btn-xs Extra small
				.component
					h3 Form submit
					p These are to denote that the action will submit or save data.
					button.btn.btn-success Default
				.component
					h3 + Glyphicon
					p Adding a universal symbol can make the action clearer and more understandable.
					button.btn.btn-primary.btn-xs
						span.glyphicon.glyphicon-save aria-hidden="true"
						|  Save glyphicon

